-- Japan Airlines Sees Over $10.9 Billion in Restructuring Costs, Nikkei Says
-- Jeran Wittenstein
-- 2010-06-14T20:13:02Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-14/japan-airlines-sees-over-10-9-billion-in-restructuring-costs-nikkei-says.html

          
          
             Japan Airlines Corp. told some banks
it has borrowed money from the airline expects more than 1
trillion yen ($10.9 billion) in restrcuturing costs related to
staff cuts and aircraft disposals, Nikkei English News reported,
without saying where it obtained the information.  
          
          


  


        